column5: Well folks got out last night for a little fish,my buddy came over and picked me up,i was out of action because of my blown cluth in my quad,which i got back today,but the $800.00 i thought it was going to be grew to $983.30,dam near had a heart attack(im excepting donations in care of a real broke Hawg Hunter),all parts, labour was only $170.00 i thought that was good,anyway heres  the story from yesterday afternoon we iced 5 walleye and i iced 1 nice fat pike that was around 6-7lbs,walleye were from 2lbs-5lbs and my buddy had one he said was the biggest one he had a chance at this year but his missed it.thats why they call it fishing and not catching well some say that.No fishing today too darn windy sorry for the double pic folks,don't know how to taker off fishing been good and is getting better  Hawg Hunter
Beautiful 'eye as always Hawg. I have plan to hit th Bay Friday afternoon with a buddy, i'd be happy if we do half as well as you guys did.  -Ramble
damn nice eyes and thats an alright pike way to go!
planning on going out wih you again on the week-end of the 8th
ya i heard that this morning,im wondering if i can pry you out of that hole this time, ,boy you were lucky eh.  glad to have ya aboard again taker easy ill see ya soon  Hawg Hunter
Nice catch !!!!!!...  well you sure have the bay of quinte all figured out , well done
